In 2023, this may be caused because of TestContainers &quot;bug&quot; where it exposes the classes from AWS SDK 1.x Core through it&#39;s own API, while you use AWS SDK 2.x

See https://github.com/testcontainers/testcontainers-java/issues/1442 

The workaround is to include the 1.x as a test dependency, too.

```xml
        &lt;dependency&gt; &lt;!-- Localstack depends on 1.x internally. --&gt;
        &lt;groupId&gt;com.amazonaws&lt;/groupId&gt;
            &lt;artifactId&gt;aws-java-sdk-core&lt;/artifactId&gt;
            &lt;version&gt;1.12.402&lt;/version&gt;
            &lt;scope&gt;test&lt;/scope&gt;
            &lt;exclusions&gt;&lt;exclusion&gt;&lt;groupId&gt;*&lt;/groupId&gt;&lt;artifactId&gt;*&lt;/artifactId&gt;&lt;/exclusion&gt;&lt;/exclusions&gt;
        &lt;/dependency&gt;
```

