## Configurative generator strategy

You seem to be implementing a [programmatic generator strategy][1], just to let you know that there&#39;s also an option of a [configurative strategy][2], which could look like this:

```xml
&lt;configuration&gt;
  &lt;generator&gt;
    &lt;strategy&gt;
      &lt;matchers&gt;
        &lt;tables&gt;
          &lt;table&gt;
            &lt;expression&gt;MY_TABLE&lt;/expression&gt;
            &lt;pojoImplements&gt;com.example.MyOptionalCustomInterface&lt;/pojoImplements&gt;
          &lt;/table&gt;
        &lt;/tables&gt;
        ...
```

[Please refer to the manual][2] for more details. In order to apply this only to tables containing certain fields, just update the regular expression in `&lt;expression&gt;` to match those tables.


```xml
&lt;expression&gt;MY_TABLE1|MY_TABLE2&lt;/expression&gt;
```

This expression has to be updated to be in sync with the schema, of course.

## Programmatic genenerator strategy

Just like with the configurative strategy, you&#39;ll have to limit yourself to applying your logic only to generated POJOs. For this, notice the remark in the [manual][1]:

```java
/**
 * ...
 * Beware that most methods also receive a &quot;Mode&quot; object, to tell you whether a
 * TableDefinition is being rendered as a Table, Record, POJO, etc. Depending on
 * that information, you can add a suffix only for TableRecords, not for Tables
 * ...
 */
```

So, you&#39;ll have to do something like this:

```java
@Override
public List&lt;String&gt; getJavaClassImplements(Definition definition, Mode mode) {
    if (mode == Mode.POJO)
        return Arrays.asList(&quot;com.example.MyOptionalCustomInterface&quot;);
    else
        return Collections.emptyList();
}
```

If you want to make sure that this inteface is only added to tables that match certain conditions, do this, instead:


```java
@Override
public List&lt;String&gt; getJavaClassImplements(Definition definition, Mode mode) {
    if (mode == Mode.POJO
            &amp;&amp; definition instanceof TableDefinition t
            &amp;&amp; t.getColumns().stream().anyMatch(c -&gt; conditionHere(c)))
        return Arrays.asList(&quot;com.example.MyOptionalCustomInterface&quot;);
    else
        return Collections.emptyList();
}
```

  [1]: https://www.jooq.org/doc/latest/manual/code-generation/codegen-generatorstrategy/
  [2]: https://www.jooq.org/doc/latest/manual/code-generation/codegen-matcherstrategy/

